CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "To Live in Buffalo - Mr. and Mrs. Daniel L. Wilburn were married by the Rev. H. S. Cuff of Corinthian Baptist Church. The bride is the former Mrs. Fannie Mae Nelson.  Attendants were: Mrs. Geraldine Mott, maid-of-honor, Mrs. Vera Ghoston and Johnny Warren, best man.  Mrs. Catherine Kenley directed the wedding. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wedding party, from left: Johnny Warren, groom Daniel Wilburn wearing light colored dinner jacket, bride Fannie Mae Nelson Wilburn wearing sleeveless dress with diamond pattern and holding bouquet of carnations, Vera Ghoston, and Geraldine Mott and posed in interior with floral curtains, another version
